commentary: Jayasuriya to Asghar Afghan, OUT huge appeal for lbw and umpire Ahsan Raza gives it out. Two wickets in two overs for Sri Lanka and both the result of batsmen being bamboozled by spin. Here Asghar is just a touch slow to react to a slider that pins him in front of middle before he's ready to play a shot. Worse, that shot is a flick, with the bat coming around his front pad, which always takes too much time

commentary: Gulbadin Naib to de Silva, 1 run, OUT huge run out chance missed! Or wait. There has been a run out in one end, but they miss it at the other end. Deliberately pokes at a wide length ball and gets an outside edge to third man. There is miscommunication on the second run. Dhananjaya is at the same end as Tharanga who is very late in responding. They are nearly at the same end, but Shahzad has taken the bails off with Dhananjaya still nearing the crease. Shahzad completes the run out and then turns around and flicks the ball to the bowler's end where Naib makes a complete mess by running across and falling on the stumps before he can get his hands on it. That's the most convoluted sequence I have ever seen!
